Here is an example code snippet using React to create a virtual staging tool for RealEstateMall:
```javascript
import React, { useState } from 'react';
import { useThree, useLoader } from 'react-three-fiber';
import { GLTFLoader } from 'three/examples/jsm/loaders/GLTFLoader';

const VirtualStaging = ({ modelPath, stagingItems, ...props }) => {
  const { camera } = useThree();
  const [activeItem, setActiveItem] = useState(0);

  const gltf = useLoader(GLTFLoader, modelPath);

  const handleItemClick = (index) => {
    setActiveItem(index);
  };

  const { nodes } = gltf.scene;
  const { materials } = nodes;

  const stagingItem = stagingItems[activeItem];

  return (
    <group {...props}>
      <primitive object={gltf.scene} />
      {stagingItems.map((item, index) => (
        <mesh key={index} position={[item.x, item.y, item.z]} onClick={() => handleItemClick(index)}>
          <boxBufferGeometry args={[item.width, item.height, item.depth]} />
          <meshStandardMaterial color={activeItem === index ? 'white' : 'grey'} />
        </mesh>
      ))}
      <mesh {...stagingItem} material={materials.virtualStaging} />
    </group>
  );
};

export default VirtualStaging;
```
This code imports React, along with the `useThree` and `useLoader` hooks from `react-three-fiber`, and the `GLTFLoader` from `three/examples/jsm/loaders/GLTFLoader`. The `VirtualStaging` component takes a `modelPath` prop, which is the path to the 3D model of the property, and a `stagingItems` prop, which is an array of objects representing the virtual staging items (furniture, decor, etc.).

The `useState` hook is used to keep track of the active virtual staging item, and the `useLoader` hook is used to load the 3D model.

The `handleItemClick` function is called when a virtual staging item is clicked, and sets the active item state.

The `nodes` and `materials` variables are used to access the nodes and materials of the 3D model, and the `stagingItem` variable is used to get the active virtual staging item.

The `group` and `primitive` components are used to render the 3D model and the virtual staging items, respectively. The `mesh` components are used to render the virtual staging items as boxes, and the active item is rendered as a mesh with the `virtualStaging` material.

This code can be customized to fit the specific needs and styling of the RealEstateMall website, and can be integrated with other tools and features to provide a seamless virtual staging experience for users.
